DateBareIsoOnJson
/ A date coerces against its ISO string in the language `==` path — `if %d% equals "2026-01-01"`
/ holds, the same cross-type coercion that makes `5 == "5"` true, extended to temporal types.
/ (Parts confirm the value; the equals shows coercion.)
- set %d% = "2026-01-01" as date
- set %coerced% = false
- if %d% equals "2026-01-01"
    - set %coerced% = true
- assert %coerced% is true
- assert %d.Year% equals 2026
